column5: Knife gets thinner and you get thicker.lol
Yes, i'll be there the last week of August, can't wait!!
It is a pretty lake! The first time i went through there i was putt putt slow as well but then my graph was showing approx 6 FOW so no more snail speed for me that week.

Finally got out with my wife for a day of fishing.She wanted to go on Eagle and cast for some muskies.Stopped in at Clarks bait shop on way to lake and grabbed 3 doz minnows.Launching still good just need tonback in a bit further at the dock.We cast most of morning and we noticed the weed beds are real poor due to the the rusty Grey fish that are in the system.Worst weed beds I've seen.We did manage to raise 8 fish but they were all very lazy coming to the boat and not one wanted to chase the lure in a figure 8.Lunch time we found a hump with fish in 16 ft and I spot locked on it and walleye action was very good and had hard time trying to eat lunch..burned through our minnows within tge hour.Nothing big but good action and all good pan sized fish for our supper.Took a short cut back through Canoe Narrows and had a foot off water through there so anyone planning to go through there take it easy.All in all very fun day.
Looks like a great day to me. I was stuck inside at work.
That's some shallow water, seems like last fall there was plenty of water in Canoe Narrows, i enjoy motoring through there. Thanks for posting John, i'll be there the end of August.
I normally go through there wide open but figured I'd better see how deep it was.We could use some rain,by Aug might be bare ground there.Remember you where headed to Eagle.Pine Beach right
I'll take a day fishing anytime
Looks like the knife got dirty today.
It was putt,putt, low my last time thru there cutting south , eagle is a pretty lake
Every lake is pretty up there,,except sandy lake..
My knife has been with me 30+ years.Good for many more allthough blade is a lot thinner now.
